  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1923",
  "title": "[instantsearch.js] Provide an API to customize the widget rendering",
  "body": "This is a feature proposal for instantsearch.js.\r\n\r\n## Rationale\r\n\r\nWith React-InstantSearch we’ve added the possibility to provide a complete custom rendering of the component. We want to provide the same kind of possibility for our instantsearch.js users with the following in mind:\r\n - bigger liberty for our users\r\n - less maintenance for us (less option to add when there is a new use case)\r\n - more thought leadership through constrained best practices).\r\n\r\n## Proposed API\r\n\r\nApply the same connector approach to the widgets provided by instantsearch.js:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nvar customMenu = connectMenu(function(opts, isFirstRendering) {\r\n  // this function is called during the `init` and `render` parts of the widget lifecycle\r\n  \r\n  // isFirstRendering is true when it is called from `init`\r\n  \r\n  // opts contains all the options now provided to the our current rendering. This could be later clean up if we decide to support less templates and css customization.\r\n});\r\n\r\ninstantsearch.addWidget(customMenu({\r\n  container: '#brands',\r\n  attributeName: 'brands',\r\n  limit: 3,\r\n}));\r\n```\r\n\r\n_This new implementation is only a pattern to apply on the widgets, it does not impact the current architecture. ~~It should also be fully compatible with the current instantsearch.js implementations~~ It has some impact on the current implementations of widgets, therefore it'll be released as part of a v2._\r\n\r\n## Steps\r\n \r\n\r\n - [x] Update all the widgets with the new pattern\r\n - [x] test connectors and make the first rendering consistent\r\n - [x] Iteration 2 (decouple view and business logic)\r\n - [x] Propagate widget configuration to view\r\n - [x] Document the newly added connectors\r\n",
